<%- include('partials/header', { pageTitle: 'Privacy Policy — The Florida Buzz', category: null, tickerItems: [], canonicalPath: '/privacy' }) %>

<main class="wrap">
  <article class="article-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="byline">Last updated: <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric', timeZone: 'America/New_York' }) %></p>

    <div class="article-body">
      <p>This website is owned and operated by Cartzilla LLC ("we," "us," "Florida Buzz"). This page explains what information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have.</p>

      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <p><strong>Newsletter signups:</strong> if you subscribe to our email newsletter, we store the email address you provide, solely to send you the newsletter. We don't sell or share this list with third parties.</p>
      <p><strong>Analytics:</strong> we use Google Analytics to understand how visitors use the site — pages viewed, general location (city/region level), device type, and similar. This data is aggregated and doesn't identify you personally. Google Analytics uses cookies to do this; you can opt out using the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.</p>
      <p><strong>Server logs:</strong> like most websites, our hosting provider automatically logs standard technical information (IP address, browser type, pages requested) for security and performance purposes.</p>

      <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
      <p>Some articles and guides on this site contain affiliate links, primarily through the Amazon Associates program. If you click one of these links and make a purchase, we may earn a small commission at no additional cost to you. As an Amazon Associate, we earn from qualifying purchases. We only recommend products we believe are genuinely relevant to the content.</p>

      <h2>Third-party services we use</h2>
      <p>This site is built on infrastructure and services including Google Analytics (analytics), Amazon Associates (affiliate links), and email/database providers that help us run the newsletter and store site content. Each of these providers has its own privacy practices governing data they process on our behalf.</p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>We use cookies primarily for analytics purposes, as described above. You can control or disable cookies through your browser settings; doing so may affect some site functionality.</p>

      <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>This site is not directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

      <h2>Your choices</h2>
      <p>You can unsubscribe from our newsletter at any time using the link in any newsletter email. You can also opt out of Google Analytics tracking using the browser add-on linked above.</p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy from time to time. The "last updated" date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about this policy can be sent to <a href="mailto:floridabuzzonline@gmail.com">floridabuzzonline@gmail.com</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</main>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
